She watches you over the rim of her glass for a beat too long. "You worked us both. Varga and me, played off the middle." Something that isn't quite a smile. "I'd be insulted if it weren't exactly what I'd have done. Just know I'm counting now — same as she is."
* [That's the job.]
    "It is. Right up until everyone's counting. Then it's just math."
    -> END
* [Nothing personal.]
    "It never is. That's the part that costs you."
    -> END
